Overview:

This project is a geographic visualization of Twitter data across the USA. 

A map would be generated to display how the people in different states feel about a keyword of your choice. An example would be “shopping”

Collecting public Tweets that have been tagged with geographic locations and filtering for those that contain the keyword “shopping” query term,
Assigning a sentiment (positive or negative) to each Tweet, based on all of the words it contains,
Aggregating Tweets by the state with the closest geographic center, and finally
Coloring each state according to the aggregate sentiment of its Tweets. Yellow means positive sentiment; blue means negative.



Instructions:

1. Go to the directory of Trend in Terminal or Git Bash.
2. Key in “python3 trends.py -m XXX -t YYY”, where XXX is the keyword you want to search and YYY is the data file(.txt) 
   An example would be “python3 trends.py -m christmas -t tweets2011.txt”